00:01:51.170 --> 00:01:52.212 align:middle line:90%
Or are they all the same?

00:01:52.212 --> 00:01:53.700 align:middle line:90%
Or what comes first?

00:01:53.700 --> 00:01:54.500 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:01:54.500 --> 00:01:56.900 align:middle line:84%
That's a good question,
thought, belief, and emotion,

00:01:56.900 --> 00:01:58.752 align:middle line:84%
because what is a
thought, what is

00:01:58.752 --> 00:01:59.960 align:middle line:90%
a belief, what is an emotion?

00:01:59.960 --> 00:02:01.580 align:middle line:84%
And how do they
relate to each other?

00:02:01.580 --> 00:02:06.910 align:middle line:84%
The way I would conceptualize it
is that thoughts are transient.

00:02:06.910 --> 00:02:10.250 align:middle line:90%
But beliefs are long term.

00:02:10.250 --> 00:02:12.240 align:middle line:84%
And a belief is a
pattern of thought.

00:02:12.240 --> 00:02:14.240 align:middle line:84%
So you might have
a fleeting thought.

00:02:14.240 --> 00:02:16.040 align:middle line:84%
But if you think that
thought over and over

00:02:16.040 --> 00:02:17.890 align:middle line:84%
and over again-- just
say, for example,

00:02:17.890 --> 00:02:20.480 align:middle line:84%
a thought of
self-criticism or something

00:02:20.480 --> 00:02:22.970 align:middle line:84%
you don't like about
the world or blame

00:02:22.970 --> 00:02:25.280 align:middle line:84%
you have towards somebody
else or a big system

00:02:25.280 --> 00:02:27.260 align:middle line:84%
like a government
or a corporation,

00:02:27.260 --> 00:02:30.500 align:middle line:84%
all of those thoughts, if
you hold them consistently,

00:02:30.500 --> 00:02:34.040 align:middle line:84%
can solidify into fixed
beliefs and worldview.

00:02:34.040 --> 00:02:36.290 align:middle line:84%
And so, for example,
you might initially

00:02:36.290 --> 00:02:39.560 align:middle line:84%
have the sense are things
not being good in your life,

00:02:39.560 --> 00:02:41.475 align:middle line:90%
may have adverse experiences.

00:02:41.475 --> 00:02:43.100 align:middle line:84%
And then that may
develop into a belief

00:02:43.100 --> 00:02:45.440 align:middle line:84%
that the world is
an unsafe place.

00:02:45.440 --> 00:02:48.500 align:middle line:84%
Now you're driving high
cortisol, high adrenaline.

00:02:48.500 --> 00:02:50.120 align:middle line:84%
You're triggering
gene expression

00:02:50.120 --> 00:02:52.580 align:middle line:84%
and a whole cascade
of biological events

00:02:52.580 --> 00:02:53.930 align:middle line:90%
with that belief.

00:02:53.930 --> 00:02:58.492 align:middle line:84%
If you then add emotion
and believe that strongly,

00:02:58.492 --> 00:03:00.200 align:middle line:84%
when you're passionate
about your belief,

00:03:00.200 --> 00:03:02.340 align:middle line:84%
now you're adding
fuel to the fire.

00:03:02.340 --> 00:03:05.648 align:middle line:84%
And that's when you'll see a
big increase in gene expression,

00:03:05.648 --> 00:03:07.190 align:middle line:84%
big increase in
those stress hormones

00:03:07.190 --> 00:03:08.630 align:middle line:90%
like adrenaline and cortisol.

00:03:08.630 --> 00:03:11.220 align:middle line:84%
And emotion is adding
fuel to that process.

00:03:11.220 --> 00:03:14.490 align:middle line:84%
A thought held lightly doesn't
have a lot of biological impact

00:03:14.490 --> 00:03:15.320 align:middle line:90%
on your body.

00:03:15.320 --> 00:03:18.080 align:middle line:84%
But a thought that is
backed by strong emotion

00:03:18.080 --> 00:03:20.700 align:middle line:84%
can have a huge
effect on your body.

00:03:20.700 --> 00:03:23.120 align:middle line:84%
Now over time, this produces
big, adverse effects

00:03:23.120 --> 00:03:23.920 align:middle line:90%
on the body.

00:03:23.920 --> 00:03:25.700 align:middle line:84%
And that thought
is a transient one.

00:03:25.700 --> 00:03:28.070 align:middle line:84%
So I had this
negative thought, you

00:03:28.070 --> 00:03:29.690 align:middle line:84%
might see a very
small shift and gene

00:03:29.690 --> 00:03:32.720 align:middle line:84%
expression and a small
rise in stress hormones.

00:03:32.720 --> 00:03:35.480 align:middle line:84%
But if you think that
thought persistently,

00:03:35.480 --> 00:03:39.780 align:middle line:84%
day after day after day, if it's
a belief, becomes a world view,

00:03:39.780 --> 00:03:41.450 align:middle line:90%
and you have emotion with it.

00:03:41.450 --> 00:03:43.880 align:middle line:84%
Now you're raising
your cortisol level

00:03:43.880 --> 00:03:46.740 align:middle line:90%
over and over and over again.

00:03:46.740 --> 00:03:52.220 align:middle line:84%
So high cortisol over time leads
to reduced muscle mass, reduced

00:03:52.220 --> 00:03:55.220 align:middle line:84%
bone density, increased
skin wrinkling,

00:03:55.220 --> 00:03:56.870 align:middle line:90%
degradation of digestion.

00:03:56.870 --> 00:03:59.870 align:middle line:84%
All of these things start
to be affected negatively

00:03:59.870 --> 00:04:02.990 align:middle line:84%
by those thoughts
held for a long time.

00:04:02.990 --> 00:04:05.690 align:middle line:84%
People under high stress
or high cortisol--

00:04:05.690 --> 00:04:07.430 align:middle line:84%
eventually, cortisol
literally begins

00:04:07.430 --> 00:04:11.990 align:middle line:84%
to calcify the memory and
learning centers in your brain.

00:04:11.990 --> 00:04:14.960 align:middle line:84%
Your hippocampus can get
calcium deposits on it

00:04:14.960 --> 00:04:17.040 align:middle line:84%
if you have high
cortisol over time.

00:04:17.040 --> 00:04:19.250 align:middle line:84%
Now you want calcium
in your bones and teeth

00:04:19.250 --> 00:04:20.550 align:middle line:90%
and places like that.

00:04:20.550 --> 00:04:23.330 align:middle line:84%
You do not want calcium
forming in your hippocampus,

00:04:23.330 --> 00:04:24.740 align:middle line:90%
your memory learning center.

00:04:24.740 --> 00:04:27.810 align:middle line:84%
That's exactly what happens
in stressed people over time.

00:04:27.810 --> 00:04:32.720 align:middle line:84%
So now your mind, your
consciousness fueled by emotion

00:04:32.720 --> 00:04:36.410 align:middle line:84%
is producing substantial
changes in your brain.

00:04:36.410 --> 00:04:40.610 align:middle line:84%
The software of mind is turning
into the hardware of brain.

00:04:40.610 --> 00:04:43.500 align:middle line:84%
And now you have a different
brain affected by stress.

00:04:43.500 --> 00:04:46.850 align:middle line:84%
But if you meditate,
if you do EFT tapping,

00:04:46.850 --> 00:04:49.273 align:middle line:84%
if you spend time in nature,
if you're in your heart,

00:04:49.273 --> 00:04:50.690 align:middle line:84%
if you spend time
with loved ones,

00:04:50.690 --> 00:04:53.040 align:middle line:84%
you have rich social
networks, all of these things

00:04:53.040 --> 00:04:53.840 align:middle line:90%
go into reverse.

00:04:53.840 --> 00:04:56.150 align:middle line:84%
Now you're not making
lots of cortisol.

00:04:56.150 --> 00:04:59.570 align:middle line:84%
You make lots of DHEA and
other positive hormones.

00:04:59.570 --> 00:05:02.310 align:middle line:84%
And DHEA is also called
the youthening hormone.

00:05:02.310 --> 00:05:06.710 align:middle line:84%
So now with high levels of
DHEA, all those aging signs,

00:05:06.710 --> 00:05:09.680 align:middle line:84%
all those things
go into reverse.

00:05:09.680 --> 00:05:13.280 align:middle line:84%
A happy person has high
DHEA, high oxytocin.

00:05:13.280 --> 00:05:15.710 align:middle line:84%
Oxytocin then sparks
the production

00:05:15.710 --> 00:05:18.590 align:middle line:84%
of neurochemicals like
anandamide, the bliss molecule,

00:05:18.590 --> 00:05:20.660 align:middle line:84%
in your brain, like
nitric oxide which

00:05:20.660 --> 00:05:22.430 align:middle line:90%
makes you alert in your life.

00:05:22.430 --> 00:05:24.680 align:middle line:84%
All these positive
things happen when

00:05:24.680 --> 00:05:28.340 align:middle line:84%
you are a positive thinker,
when you meditate, when you tap,

00:05:28.340 --> 00:05:30.620 align:middle line:84%
when you do all these
practices that center you

00:05:30.620 --> 00:05:33.620 align:middle line:84%
and give you a positive
affect mood outlook.

00:05:33.620 --> 00:05:37.940 align:middle line:84%
So now thought, consciousness
fueled by positive emotion

00:05:37.940 --> 00:05:39.675 align:middle line:90%
is becoming vibrant health.

00:05:39.675 --> 00:05:41.800 align:middle line:84%
And that's the direction
you want to nudge yourself

00:05:41.800 --> 00:05:42.920 align:middle line:90%
in with every thought.

00:05:42.920 --> 00:05:45.920 align:middle line:84%
People think their
thoughts are innocuous.

00:05:45.920 --> 00:05:47.400 align:middle line:84%
They think they're
insubstantial.

00:05:47.400 --> 00:05:49.567 align:middle line:84%
But they're affecting your
body every single moment.

00:05:49.567 --> 00:05:52.192 align:middle line:84%
I remember when I was working on
my book, "Genie in Your Genes"

00:05:52.192 --> 00:05:54.920 align:middle line:84%
and I was getting knee deep into
this research many years ago,

00:05:54.920 --> 00:05:56.480 align:middle line:90%
reading these studies.

00:05:56.480 --> 00:05:59.600 align:middle line:84%
One day, I was reading
a scientific paper.

00:05:59.600 --> 00:06:01.690 align:middle line:90%
And my kids were teenagers then.

00:06:01.690 --> 00:06:06.800 align:middle line:84%
And I ran out of my office,
waving a paper by my head,

00:06:06.800 --> 00:06:07.750 align:middle line:90%
brandishing this.

00:06:07.750 --> 00:06:10.610 align:middle line:84%
I said to my son,
I said, "Lionel,

00:06:10.610 --> 00:06:13.580 align:middle line:84%
if you'd read this, if
you knew what I know now,

00:06:13.580 --> 00:06:16.220 align:middle line:84%
you would never have a
single negative thought

00:06:16.220 --> 00:06:17.270 align:middle line:90%
in your entire life."

00:06:17.270 --> 00:06:22.700 align:middle line:90%


00:06:22.700 --> 00:06:26.570 align:middle line:84%
And really, if you knew the
harm it did to your body,

00:06:26.570 --> 00:06:30.470 align:middle line:84%
you would do your utmost to
quit that negative thinking

00:06:30.470 --> 00:06:32.430 align:middle line:90%
immediately.

00:06:32.430 --> 00:06:34.260 align:middle line:90%
>> And yet we don't.

00:06:34.260 --> 00:06:36.180 align:middle line:90%
It's dizzying to think.

00:06:36.180 --> 00:06:39.060 align:middle line:84%
One of the things we just
spoke before we started

00:06:39.060 --> 00:06:41.130 align:middle line:84%
this conversation
was about how much

00:06:41.130 --> 00:06:44.650 align:middle line:84%
we allow ourselves to be
conditioned by our environment.

00:06:44.650 --> 00:06:46.770 align:middle line:84%
What are the dangers
of allowing ourselves

00:06:46.770 --> 00:06:49.880 align:middle line:84%
to be overrun with thoughts and
emotions from our environment

00:06:49.880 --> 00:06:52.150 align:middle line:84%
and not really
controlling them, per se?

00:06:52.150 --> 00:06:55.230 align:middle line:90%


00:06:55.230 --> 00:06:58.440 align:middle line:84%
>> One of the depressing
statistics is how many people

00:06:58.440 --> 00:07:02.160 align:middle line:84%
check their phones first
thing in the morning.

00:07:02.160 --> 00:07:04.830 align:middle line:84%
They wake up and they look at
their social media accounts.

00:07:04.830 --> 00:07:06.870 align:middle line:84%
They check email first
thing in the morning.

00:07:06.870 --> 00:07:10.290 align:middle line:84%
And that's over half the people,
in some surveys about 2/3

00:07:10.290 --> 00:07:11.590 align:middle line:90%
of people do this.

00:07:11.590 --> 00:07:15.690 align:middle line:84%
There are studies showing that
some people check their cell

00:07:15.690 --> 00:07:18.882 align:middle line:84%
phones during
sexual intercourse.

00:07:18.882 --> 00:07:23.035 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHING]

00:07:23.035 --> 00:07:23.910 align:middle line:90%
This is an addiction.

00:07:23.910 --> 00:07:25.620 align:middle line:90%
That's addictive behavior.

00:07:25.620 --> 00:07:28.770 align:middle line:84%
We're addicted to stuff and
very little of it is positive.

00:07:28.770 --> 00:07:32.640 align:middle line:84%
So we're filling our minds with
negative news, negative inputs.

00:07:32.640 --> 00:07:34.360 align:middle line:84%
We're not taking
control of our health.

00:07:34.360 --> 00:07:35.950 align:middle line:84%
We're handing
control of our health

00:07:35.950 --> 00:07:37.950 align:middle line:84%
and our thoughts and our
beliefs to other people

00:07:37.950 --> 00:07:39.120 align:middle line:90%
outside of ourselves.

00:07:39.120 --> 00:07:42.720 align:middle line:84%
And we're handing our thoughts
and control of our beliefs

00:07:42.720 --> 00:07:46.830 align:middle line:84%
over to people who just want to
make a buck off negative news.

00:07:46.830 --> 00:07:50.490 align:middle line:84%
So one study, for example,
looked at the world.

00:07:50.490 --> 00:07:53.950 align:middle line:84%
And it compared the world
to news about the world.

00:07:53.950 --> 00:07:56.880 align:middle line:84%
Now if you look at
actual objective measures

00:07:56.880 --> 00:07:59.280 align:middle line:84%
of human flourishing,
they're fantastic.

00:07:59.280 --> 00:08:02.310 align:middle line:84%
In the last 33 years,
human global wealth

00:08:02.310 --> 00:08:04.680 align:middle line:84%
for the average
citizen has tripled.

00:08:04.680 --> 00:08:08.490 align:middle line:84%
Over the last century, the
human lifespan has, on average,

00:08:08.490 --> 00:08:09.810 align:middle line:90%
doubled.

00:08:09.810 --> 00:08:15.810 align:middle line:84%
We now have about half the
CO2 production per unit of GDP

00:08:15.810 --> 00:08:17.560 align:middle line:90%
we had 20 years ago.

00:08:17.560 --> 00:08:20.490 align:middle line:84%
If you look at human rights, if
you look at infant mortality,

00:08:20.490 --> 00:08:23.220 align:middle line:84%
virtually every
measure of flourishing

00:08:23.220 --> 00:08:25.080 align:middle line:90%
shows we're improving.

00:08:25.080 --> 00:08:29.220 align:middle line:84%
Globally, IQ is rising by about
three points every decade.

00:08:29.220 --> 00:08:31.380 align:middle line:84%
So if you just look
at all the statistics,

00:08:31.380 --> 00:08:35.190 align:middle line:84%
everything points to us
being an unprecedented era

00:08:35.190 --> 00:08:36.270 align:middle line:90%
of human flourishing.

00:08:36.270 --> 00:08:40.289 align:middle line:84%
Now what's happening in
the media is the opposite.

00:08:40.289 --> 00:08:43.679 align:middle line:84%
One team of scientists did
a word analysis of words

00:08:43.679 --> 00:08:44.880 align:middle line:90%
in the New York Times.

00:08:44.880 --> 00:08:47.105 align:middle line:84%
They did from 1945
to the present.

00:08:47.105 --> 00:08:49.230 align:middle line:84%
And of course, we have
records going back that long

00:08:49.230 --> 00:08:50.450 align:middle line:90%
with the New York Times.

00:08:50.450 --> 00:08:53.850 align:middle line:84%
And they found that over the
years, the number of words

00:08:53.850 --> 00:09:00.600 align:middle line:84%
like good and positive,
happy, all of those words

00:09:00.600 --> 00:09:02.460 align:middle line:90%
were in steady decline.

00:09:02.460 --> 00:09:06.780 align:middle line:84%
And words like horrific
and tragic and violent,

00:09:06.780 --> 00:09:09.100 align:middle line:84%
all these negative
words were going up.

00:09:09.100 --> 00:09:13.650 align:middle line:84%
Even as the actual state of the
world is in improving steadily,

00:09:13.650 --> 00:09:16.650 align:middle line:84%
our perception of it, as
portrayed by the media,

00:09:16.650 --> 00:09:18.570 align:middle line:90%
is getting worse.

00:09:18.570 --> 00:09:21.660 align:middle line:84%
In fact, that same team,
they looked at word analysis

00:09:21.660 --> 00:09:25.277 align:middle line:84%
from 130 countries, all
their media since 1975.

00:09:25.277 --> 00:09:26.610 align:middle line:90%
And they found the same pattern.

00:09:26.610 --> 00:09:28.110 align:middle line:84%
All over the world,
we're being told

00:09:28.110 --> 00:09:29.610 align:middle line:84%
things are worse
and worse and worse

00:09:29.610 --> 00:09:31.735 align:middle line:84%
while they're getting better
and better and better.

00:09:31.735 --> 00:09:34.350 align:middle line:84%
And so what happens when
we wake up in the morning

00:09:34.350 --> 00:09:38.430 align:middle line:84%
and we then hand our
conscience over to Facebook

00:09:38.430 --> 00:09:42.810 align:middle line:84%
and Google and Instagram and
all these external sources?

00:09:42.810 --> 00:09:45.990 align:middle line:84%
We're then saying, you've got
to program my mind for me.

00:09:45.990 --> 00:09:49.350 align:middle line:84%
And you're getting a completely
inaccurate view of the world

00:09:49.350 --> 00:09:50.400 align:middle line:90%
by doing that.

00:09:50.400 --> 00:09:52.135 align:middle line:84%
What I recommend
you do instead--

00:09:52.135 --> 00:09:55.590 align:middle line:84%
what I do every morning is,
I wake up in the morning.

00:09:55.590 --> 00:09:58.180 align:middle line:84%
And immediately, I
attune to what I call

00:09:58.180 --> 00:10:00.120 align:middle line:90%
in my books non-local mind.

00:10:00.120 --> 00:10:01.800 align:middle line:90%
We have our consciousness.

00:10:01.800 --> 00:10:05.280 align:middle line:84%
But our consciousness is not
the artifact of a complex brain.

00:10:05.280 --> 00:10:07.830 align:middle line:84%
Our brain is more
like a transceiver

00:10:07.830 --> 00:10:09.870 align:middle line:84%
of information from
non-local fields

00:10:09.870 --> 00:10:12.960 align:middle line:84%
and a translator of that
information into local reality.

00:10:12.960 --> 00:10:16.290 align:middle line:84%
We literally make up
local reality around us

00:10:16.290 --> 00:10:17.340 align:middle line:90%
with our brains.

00:10:17.340 --> 00:10:21.170 align:middle line:84%
So if you wake up in the
morning and you, of course,

00:10:21.170 --> 00:10:23.230 align:middle line:84%
have a local mind,
you have a local body.

00:10:23.230 --> 00:10:27.110 align:middle line:84%
But if you immediately
attune it to non-local mind,

00:10:27.110 --> 00:10:30.240 align:middle line:84%
non-local reality, then
the news you're getting

00:10:30.240 --> 00:10:31.600 align:middle line:90%
is the news of the universe.

00:10:31.600 --> 00:10:32.580 align:middle line:90%
And it is positive.

00:10:32.580 --> 00:10:36.090 align:middle line:84%
It is full of abundance and
love and compassion and joy.

00:10:36.090 --> 00:10:38.520 align:middle line:84%
So now, you're plugging
yourself into all of that.

00:10:38.520 --> 00:10:41.100 align:middle line:84%
You aren't plugging yourself
into all the negative media,

00:10:41.100 --> 00:10:43.860 align:middle line:84%
the negative inputs and
filling your mind with that.

00:10:43.860 --> 00:10:45.700 align:middle line:90%
You're plugging into reality.

00:10:45.700 --> 00:10:48.360 align:middle line:84%
That stuff out there
is not reality.

00:10:48.360 --> 00:10:50.220 align:middle line:90%
This stuff up here is reality.

00:10:50.220 --> 00:10:53.190 align:middle line:84%
The mystics, the saints,
the sages throughout history

00:10:53.190 --> 00:10:57.270 align:middle line:84%
have told us that you lose
yourself in an ocean of bliss

00:10:57.270 --> 00:10:58.590 align:middle line:90%
when you're there.

00:10:58.590 --> 00:11:00.210 align:middle line:84%
Now what starts
happening in your body

00:11:00.210 --> 00:11:04.290 align:middle line:84%
then is not high cortisol,
is not high adrenaline.

00:11:04.290 --> 00:11:06.030 align:middle line:90%
It's high DHEA.

00:11:06.030 --> 00:11:07.500 align:middle line:90%
It's high oxytocin.

00:11:07.500 --> 00:11:10.290 align:middle line:84%
It's high anandamide,
the bliss molecule.

00:11:10.290 --> 00:11:12.090 align:middle line:90%
It is nitric oxide.

00:11:12.090 --> 00:11:15.360 align:middle line:84%
It is norepinephrine,
which helps you stay alert.

00:11:15.360 --> 00:11:18.090 align:middle line:84%
All these beneficial
shifts happen in your body.

00:11:18.090 --> 00:11:19.850 align:middle line:84%
Your brain secretes
beta endorphins.

00:11:19.850 --> 00:11:21.630 align:middle line:84%
So you begin a
meditation practice.

00:11:21.630 --> 00:11:24.510 align:middle line:84%
Beta endorphins are the
natural form of morphine.

00:11:24.510 --> 00:11:26.640 align:middle line:84%
They are three
times more powerful

00:11:26.640 --> 00:11:27.785 align:middle line:90%
than synthetic morphine.

00:11:27.785 --> 00:11:29.910 align:middle line:84%
So now you see, you start
your meditation practice.

00:11:29.910 --> 00:11:31.560 align:middle line:84%
You feel a bit of
ache in your back.

00:11:31.560 --> 00:11:32.603 align:middle line:90%
Your tummy's rumbling.

00:11:32.603 --> 00:11:34.020 align:middle line:84%
If you feel a
little bit of a neck

00:11:34.020 --> 00:11:36.720 align:middle line:84%
ache from exercising
too much yesterday.

00:11:36.720 --> 00:11:38.400 align:middle line:90%
And suddenly, you're in bliss.

00:11:38.400 --> 00:11:40.050 align:middle line:84%
You've forgotten
about your body.

00:11:40.050 --> 00:11:41.820 align:middle line:84%
That's beta
endorphin kicking in.

00:11:41.820 --> 00:11:44.860 align:middle line:84%
So you now have all
these beneficial hormones

00:11:44.860 --> 00:11:47.460 align:middle line:84%
and neurotransmitters kicking
in because you plugged yourself

00:11:47.460 --> 00:11:49.560 align:middle line:84%
into the information source
of the universe, which

00:11:49.560 --> 00:11:53.440 align:middle line:84%
has nothing but love for you and
love for everything around you.

00:11:53.440 --> 00:11:55.330 align:middle line:84%
So that's how you want
to start your day.

00:11:55.330 --> 00:11:57.527 align:middle line:84%
And those are the beneficial
biological changes

00:11:57.527 --> 00:11:59.110 align:middle line:84%
you want to be
producing in your body,

00:11:59.110 --> 00:12:01.240 align:middle line:84%
not all these negative
ones that come

00:12:01.240 --> 00:12:03.700 align:middle line:84%
from plugging in to
the outside world

00:12:03.700 --> 00:12:07.810 align:middle line:84%
to these thoughts and ideas
and worldviews and stories that

00:12:07.810 --> 00:12:09.690 align:middle line:90%
come from the news.

00:12:09.690 --> 00:12:10.490 align:middle line:90%
>> Beautiful.

00:12:10.490 --> 00:12:14.350 align:middle line:84%
And I think that goes a
long way to describing

00:12:14.350 --> 00:12:16.540 align:middle line:84%
in a scientific way,
what happens when people

00:12:16.540 --> 00:12:18.760 align:middle line:90%
have a spiritual experience.

00:12:18.760 --> 00:12:22.655 align:middle line:84%
I want to talk a little bit more
on your "Genie in Your Genes"

00:12:22.655 --> 00:12:24.280 align:middle line:84%
work, because I
thought that was really

00:12:24.280 --> 00:12:26.020 align:middle line:84%
foundational in
helping us understand

00:12:26.020 --> 00:12:27.340 align:middle line:90%
the power of epigenetics.

00:12:27.340 --> 00:12:30.370 align:middle line:84%
Because we have bought into
this idea that we are victims,

00:12:30.370 --> 00:12:31.740 align:middle line:90%
we're victims to our genes.

00:12:31.740 --> 00:12:33.490 align:middle line:84%
And that if we get
something, well, that's

00:12:33.490 --> 00:12:36.010 align:middle line:84%
because my mom had it
and my mom's had it.

00:12:36.010 --> 00:12:38.980 align:middle line:84%
And that's simply not
true with the research

00:12:38.980 --> 00:12:40.990 align:middle line:84%
that you're helping
bring to prominence.

00:12:40.990 --> 00:12:42.970 align:middle line:84%
What is the study
of epigenetics?

00:12:42.970 --> 00:12:45.160 align:middle line:84%
And how can we understand
it more deeply in order

00:12:45.160 --> 00:12:47.500 align:middle line:90%
to re-empower ourselves?

00:12:47.500 --> 00:12:55.510 align:middle line:84%
>> So epigenetics is changes in
genes triggered by factors that

00:12:55.510 --> 00:13:00.410 align:middle line:84%
come from outside the genome
and often, outside the body.

00:13:00.410 --> 00:13:03.070 align:middle line:84%
And a simple
example is that, say

00:13:03.070 --> 00:13:04.930 align:middle line:84%
you're walking through
the park one day.

00:13:04.930 --> 00:13:06.480 align:middle line:90%
It's a beautiful summer's day.

00:13:06.480 --> 00:13:08.020 align:middle line:90%
You're feeling wonderful.

00:13:08.020 --> 00:13:11.650 align:middle line:84%
And then a pitbull breaks
loose of its owner,

00:13:11.650 --> 00:13:15.760 align:middle line:84%
rushes over to you with
fangs open, mouth open,

00:13:15.760 --> 00:13:20.020 align:middle line:84%
fangs dripping with saliva,
just barking furiously at you,

00:13:20.020 --> 00:13:21.220 align:middle line:90%
running into you.

00:13:21.220 --> 00:13:23.920 align:middle line:90%
Suddenly, your whole day shifts.

00:13:23.920 --> 00:13:25.660 align:middle line:84%
You then move into
fight or flight

00:13:25.660 --> 00:13:28.220 align:middle line:84%
and you're going to react to
this threat from the outside.

00:13:28.220 --> 00:13:31.750 align:middle line:84%
So your body is translating
this external stimulus

00:13:31.750 --> 00:13:35.800 align:middle line:84%
of the pitbull into internal
biochemical molecular

00:13:35.800 --> 00:13:36.722 align:middle line:90%
messengers.

00:13:36.722 --> 00:13:38.680 align:middle line:84%
And those are going
throughout your whole body.

00:13:38.680 --> 00:13:41.320 align:middle line:84%
And they're pushing
you into stress, not

00:13:41.320 --> 00:13:43.900 align:middle line:90%
in 20 seconds or five minutes.

00:13:43.900 --> 00:13:45.190 align:middle line:90%
That's too late.

00:13:45.190 --> 00:13:47.470 align:middle line:84%
Those genes reach
peak expression

00:13:47.470 --> 00:13:49.420 align:middle line:90%
in under three seconds.

00:13:49.420 --> 00:13:51.280 align:middle line:84%
So now your body's
flooded with adrenaline,

00:13:51.280 --> 00:13:53.280 align:middle line:84%
flooded with cortisol
very, very quickly.

00:13:53.280 --> 00:13:55.490 align:middle line:84%
And you're then
responding to that threat.

00:13:55.490 --> 00:13:58.600 align:middle line:84%
So that's how this
works epigenetically

00:13:58.600 --> 00:14:03.160 align:middle line:84%
and how an external stimulus can
produce an internal response.

00:14:03.160 --> 00:14:06.400 align:middle line:84%
Now that's the way the stress
response is meant to work.

00:14:06.400 --> 00:14:08.500 align:middle line:84%
Our ancestors survived
because they had a hair

00:14:08.500 --> 00:14:10.720 align:middle line:90%
trigger stress response.

00:14:10.720 --> 00:14:13.420 align:middle line:84%
And in any tribe, any ancient
tribe 100,000 years ago,

00:14:13.420 --> 00:14:17.670 align:middle line:84%
500,000 years ago, those people
with the best stress response,

00:14:17.670 --> 00:14:20.980 align:middle line:84%
with the best ability to turn
those genes on in a flash

00:14:20.980 --> 00:14:24.080 align:middle line:84%
and make lots of adrenaline,
those people lived.

00:14:24.080 --> 00:14:26.990 align:middle line:84%
The happy people
like you or me ?

00:14:26.990 --> 00:14:27.790 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHS]

00:14:27.790 --> 00:14:29.383 align:middle line:84%
The Vikings marauded
and they died

00:14:29.383 --> 00:14:31.550 align:middle line:84%
because they didn't have
that quick stress response.

00:14:31.550 --> 00:14:32.890 align:middle line:84%
The meditators, you
know, they were just

00:14:32.890 --> 00:14:35.015 align:middle line:84%
sitting there in the cave
and they got slaughtered.

00:14:35.015 --> 00:14:38.050 align:middle line:84%
So we've been bred
now for millennia

00:14:38.050 --> 00:14:41.860 align:middle line:84%
to have a lightning fast stress
response, which was perfect

00:14:41.860 --> 00:14:44.290 align:middle line:84%
when there were tigers and
mastodons and all kinds

00:14:44.290 --> 00:14:45.880 align:middle line:90%
of predators around us.

00:14:45.880 --> 00:14:50.730 align:middle line:84%
Now the worst
predator we have is

00:14:50.730 --> 00:14:52.800 align:middle line:90%
our thinking, our own thoughts.

00:14:52.800 --> 00:14:54.930 align:middle line:90%
So now I go back home.

00:14:54.930 --> 00:14:59.400 align:middle line:84%
The pitbull event
is five hours old.

00:14:59.400 --> 00:15:02.100 align:middle line:84%
I didn't get injured,
nothing bad happened.

00:15:02.100 --> 00:15:06.390 align:middle line:84%
And I'm telling the story to
my child and I'm getting upset.

00:15:06.390 --> 00:15:08.730 align:middle line:84%
I can feel my
heart racing faster

00:15:08.730 --> 00:15:09.960 align:middle line:90%
as I think about the pitbull.

00:15:09.960 --> 00:15:11.550 align:middle line:90%
My face is flushing.

00:15:11.550 --> 00:15:14.220 align:middle line:84%
I am having the
same stress response

00:15:14.220 --> 00:15:16.950 align:middle line:84%
in response to my own
thinking and emotion

00:15:16.950 --> 00:15:18.480 align:middle line:90%
as I had to the pitbull.

00:15:18.480 --> 00:15:20.880 align:middle line:84%
And again, if we do
that over and over

00:15:20.880 --> 00:15:25.530 align:middle line:84%
and over again, if we retell the
sad, tragic story of our past,

00:15:25.530 --> 00:15:28.530 align:middle line:84%
if we stay stuck
in our childhood

00:15:28.530 --> 00:15:30.960 align:middle line:84%
traumas and the unresolved
issues of our past,

00:15:30.960 --> 00:15:33.090 align:middle line:84%
if we remain there over
and over and over again,

00:15:33.090 --> 00:15:35.350 align:middle line:84%
it has a terrible
effect on our bodies.

00:15:35.350 --> 00:15:37.650 align:middle line:84%
One of the studies in my
book, "Mind to Matter"

00:15:37.650 --> 00:15:41.220 align:middle line:84%
compares the lifespan of
optimists versus pessimists.

00:15:41.220 --> 00:15:45.420 align:middle line:84%
People who have a cheery and
positive frame for their lives,

00:15:45.420 --> 00:15:48.150 align:middle line:84%
they have all the same
problems as other people.

00:15:48.150 --> 00:15:50.070 align:middle line:90%
They may have been fired a job.

00:15:50.070 --> 00:15:51.690 align:middle line:84%
They may have had
a financial crash.

00:15:51.690 --> 00:15:54.790 align:middle line:84%
They may have had all
kinds of personal problems.

00:15:54.790 --> 00:15:57.440 align:middle line:84%
But they have an optimistic
take on the world.

00:15:57.440 --> 00:16:00.870 align:middle line:84%
It compares their
lifespan to pessimists.

00:16:00.870 --> 00:16:07.110 align:middle line:84%
And the difference in lifespan
is eight years, eight years.

00:16:07.110 --> 00:16:11.610 align:middle line:84%
Those optimists live eight
years longer than pessimists.

00:16:11.610 --> 00:16:13.530 align:middle line:84%
And those aren't
eight years spent

00:16:13.530 --> 00:16:15.360 align:middle line:84%
on a respirator
in a nursing home.

00:16:15.360 --> 00:16:18.060 align:middle line:84%
Those are eight
healthy years as well.

00:16:18.060 --> 00:16:19.680 align:middle line:84%
So just think about
that for a moment.

00:16:19.680 --> 00:16:24.240 align:middle line:84%
Just the way you hold things
may not be that apparent to you

00:16:24.240 --> 00:16:25.940 align:middle line:90%
when you're 20 or 30.

00:16:25.940 --> 00:16:28.115 align:middle line:84%
But when you're
40 and 50 and 60,

00:16:28.115 --> 00:16:29.490 align:middle line:84%
you start thinking
very seriously

00:16:29.490 --> 00:16:32.140 align:middle line:84%
about those last eight years
and the quality of life

00:16:32.140 --> 00:16:33.390 align:middle line:90%
you have in those eight years.

00:16:33.390 --> 00:16:35.400 align:middle line:84%
That's going to be
radically shifted

00:16:35.400 --> 00:16:39.640 align:middle line:84%
by your thoughts and
your emotions right now.

00:16:39.640 --> 00:16:42.280 align:middle line:84%
>> That's easy to say for
someone who is inherently

00:16:42.280 --> 00:16:45.730 align:middle line:84%
optimistic or grew up in a nice
household with a comfortable

00:16:45.730 --> 00:16:46.780 align:middle line:90%
life.

00:16:46.780 --> 00:16:49.690 align:middle line:84%
But what about someone
who was abused?

00:16:49.690 --> 00:16:54.930 align:middle line:84%
What about somebody who had
sexual abuse as a child?

00:16:54.930 --> 00:16:57.130 align:middle line:84%
What about somebody who
was beaten as a child?

00:16:57.130 --> 00:17:00.520 align:middle line:84%
What about somebody who
was neglected or abandoned

00:17:00.520 --> 00:17:03.220 align:middle line:84%
and not loved and is
now out in the world,

00:17:03.220 --> 00:17:05.170 align:middle line:84%
playing out the way
that they're responding

00:17:05.170 --> 00:17:06.250 align:middle line:90%
to that in adulthood?

00:17:06.250 --> 00:17:09.490 align:middle line:84%
How can they become
aware of these emotions?

00:17:09.490 --> 00:17:11.109 align:middle line:90%
And what can they do about them?

00:17:11.109 --> 00:17:12.490 align:middle line:84%
>> There are two
kinds of trauma.

00:17:12.490 --> 00:17:15.130 align:middle line:84%
There is simple trauma and
there's complex trauma.

00:17:15.130 --> 00:17:18.130 align:middle line:84%
And complex trauma is
usually developmental trauma.

00:17:18.130 --> 00:17:19.720 align:middle line:84%
So an example of
simple trauma is,

00:17:19.720 --> 00:17:22.960 align:middle line:84%
somebody who's 25 years old,
they have a terrible car crash.

00:17:22.960 --> 00:17:25.730 align:middle line:84%
And they're in the
hospital for a long time.

00:17:25.730 --> 00:17:27.250 align:middle line:84%
It takes them a
great many months

00:17:27.250 --> 00:17:28.780 align:middle line:90%
to regain physical function.

00:17:28.780 --> 00:17:31.510 align:middle line:84%
And this shatters their lives
in some fundamental way.

00:17:31.510 --> 00:17:33.340 align:middle line:90%
That's a simple trauma.

00:17:33.340 --> 00:17:37.690 align:middle line:84%
A complex trauma is one
where there was abuse,

00:17:37.690 --> 00:17:38.830 align:middle line:90%
often as a child.

00:17:38.830 --> 00:17:40.647 align:middle line:84%
And if there's
developmental trauma

00:17:40.647 --> 00:17:42.730 align:middle line:84%
where you were beaten over
and over and over again

00:17:42.730 --> 00:17:45.490 align:middle line:84%
or whether you were being
neglected, whether you were

00:17:45.490 --> 00:17:48.160 align:middle line:84%
being raped, whether you were
being physically assaulted,

00:17:48.160 --> 00:17:49.348 align:middle line:90%
and it was repeated.

00:17:49.348 --> 00:17:50.890 align:middle line:84%
And that's a different
kind of trauma

00:17:50.890 --> 00:17:56.780 align:middle line:84%
because the brain is growing
while that trauma is happening.

00:17:56.780 --> 00:17:59.290 align:middle line:84%
And that information is
being installed at the level

00:17:59.290 --> 00:18:01.090 align:middle line:90%
of circuits in your brain.

00:18:01.090 --> 00:18:04.760 align:middle line:84%
It's not just a thought
or a belief or one event.

00:18:04.760 --> 00:18:08.620 align:middle line:84%
It is crucial, it is
fundamental to the actual way

00:18:08.620 --> 00:18:10.210 align:middle line:90%
your brain wired together.

00:18:10.210 --> 00:18:13.390 align:middle line:84%
For the first two years of life,
the fastest growing rate brain

00:18:13.390 --> 00:18:15.350 align:middle line:90%
region is the limbic system.

00:18:15.350 --> 00:18:17.230 align:middle line:84%
So the limbic system,
the emotional midbrain

00:18:17.230 --> 00:18:19.390 align:middle line:84%
is the fastest
growing brain region.

00:18:19.390 --> 00:18:22.690 align:middle line:84%
It's not a part of the
brain that has language.

00:18:22.690 --> 00:18:25.550 align:middle line:84%
That's Broca's area over
here behind our temple.

00:18:25.550 --> 00:18:26.740 align:middle line:90%
That's the language part.

00:18:26.740 --> 00:18:29.545 align:middle line:84%
This is the center of our
brain, the emotional midbrain,

00:18:29.545 --> 00:18:31.420 align:middle line:84%
that's the fastest
growing part of our brain.

00:18:31.420 --> 00:18:35.810 align:middle line:84%
It has no language but it
feels and feels deeply.

00:18:35.810 --> 00:18:38.350 align:middle line:84%
And so if you're
being traumatized

00:18:38.350 --> 00:18:41.230 align:middle line:84%
while that part of
your brain is growing,

00:18:41.230 --> 00:18:46.210 align:middle line:84%
then trauma is woven into
the neural fabric of the way

00:18:46.210 --> 00:18:47.800 align:middle line:90%
your brain structure is.

00:18:47.800 --> 00:18:50.200 align:middle line:84%
And so that kind of
trauma is hard to treat.

00:18:50.200 --> 00:18:52.510 align:middle line:84%
We find in trauma
treatment manuals

00:18:52.510 --> 00:18:56.110 align:middle line:84%
and approaches that simple
trauma is relatively easy,

00:18:56.110 --> 00:18:58.870 align:middle line:84%
but developmental
trauma, complex trauma

00:18:58.870 --> 00:19:00.610 align:middle line:90%
is hard to treat.

00:19:00.610 --> 00:19:02.980 align:middle line:84%
So how does that
person get through it?

00:19:02.980 --> 00:19:07.090 align:middle line:84%
And you can't easily get through
it using cognitive techniques,

00:19:07.090 --> 00:19:09.610 align:middle line:84%
using thought or
language based therapies.

00:19:09.610 --> 00:19:12.400 align:middle line:84%
I can't sit you in
a chair and say,

00:19:12.400 --> 00:19:14.110 align:middle line:84%
you shouldn't feel
that way, because it's

00:19:14.110 --> 00:19:16.540 align:middle line:84%
fundamental to the way
your brain functions.

00:19:16.540 --> 00:19:18.640 align:middle line:84%
So for example, there
was a famous psychiatrist

00:19:18.640 --> 00:19:19.990 align:middle line:90%
called Joseph Wolpe.

00:19:19.990 --> 00:19:23.260 align:middle line:84%
After World War
II, he was working

00:19:23.260 --> 00:19:25.090 align:middle line:90%
with veterans of World War II.

00:19:25.090 --> 00:19:29.440 align:middle line:84%
And these men, for the most
part men, had shell shock.

00:19:29.440 --> 00:19:32.368 align:middle line:84%
They were dreadfully
affected by the war.

00:19:32.368 --> 00:19:33.910 align:middle line:84%
And he was a good
Freudian therapist.

00:19:33.910 --> 00:19:37.060 align:middle line:84%
So he laid them on the couch to
do the talking cure and said,

00:19:37.060 --> 00:19:41.470 align:middle line:90%
tell me about Omaha Beach.

00:19:41.470 --> 00:19:43.120 align:middle line:84%
And he wrote in
one of his books,

00:19:43.120 --> 00:19:45.430 align:middle line:84%
he said, he came
to the realization

00:19:45.430 --> 00:19:48.010 align:middle line:84%
after doing this with
those soldiers, he said,

00:19:48.010 --> 00:19:52.390 align:middle line:84%
that kind of therapy
is not ineffective.

00:19:52.390 --> 00:19:53.930 align:middle line:90%
It's harmful.

00:19:53.930 --> 00:19:58.690 align:middle line:84%
And a later term, it's
re-traumatizing to remember

00:19:58.690 --> 00:20:00.670 align:middle line:84%
the bad stuff, to remember
the pitbull attack,

00:20:00.670 --> 00:20:02.128 align:middle line:84%
remember the car
accident, remember

00:20:02.128 --> 00:20:04.510 align:middle line:84%
your buddies was being
blown to bits on the beach.

00:20:04.510 --> 00:20:09.820 align:middle line:84%
By replaying that in your mind,
that thought, now stimulating

00:20:09.820 --> 00:20:13.150 align:middle line:84%
that emotion is actually
re-traumatizing you.

00:20:13.150 --> 00:20:16.960 align:middle line:84%
And as you fire those neural
circuits in your brain,

00:20:16.960 --> 00:20:19.390 align:middle line:84%
they wire together bigger
and bigger and bigger.

00:20:19.390 --> 00:20:22.570 align:middle line:84%
So we find, for example,
that stress circuits

00:20:22.570 --> 00:20:25.390 align:middle line:84%
like the amygdala grow
in people who have

00:20:25.390 --> 00:20:26.980 align:middle line:90%
been traumatized in that way.

00:20:26.980 --> 00:20:30.430 align:middle line:84%
And learning and memory circuits
like those in the hippocampus

00:20:30.430 --> 00:20:32.420 align:middle line:90%
actually shrink over time.

00:20:32.420 --> 00:20:34.780 align:middle line:84%
So we're doing brain
remodeling with our thoughts.

00:20:34.780 --> 00:20:39.730 align:middle line:84%
Our thought aren't just
producing some kind of emotion

00:20:39.730 --> 00:20:41.620 align:middle line:90%
or experience in our minds.

00:20:41.620 --> 00:20:44.687 align:middle line:84%
They're producing neural
tissue in our brains.

00:20:44.687 --> 00:20:47.020 align:middle line:84%
And if you start to use that
neural tissue over and over

00:20:47.020 --> 00:20:49.270 align:middle line:84%
again, then it becomes
hard to change.

00:20:49.270 --> 00:20:51.490 align:middle line:84%
So you can't use
cognitive techniques

00:20:51.490 --> 00:20:54.310 align:middle line:84%
for development trauma
or preverbal trauma.

00:20:54.310 --> 00:20:55.620 align:middle line:90%
You need energy techniques.

00:20:55.620 --> 00:20:56.995 align:middle line:84%
And we have huge
numbers of them.

00:20:56.995 --> 00:21:00.310 align:middle line:84%
We have acupuncture which
affects the flows of energy

00:21:00.310 --> 00:21:01.580 align:middle line:90%
in the body's meridians.

00:21:01.580 --> 00:21:03.730 align:middle line:84%
We have acupressure
like EFT where

00:21:03.730 --> 00:21:06.970 align:middle line:84%
you interrupt that thought and
that experience with pressure

00:21:06.970 --> 00:21:08.380 align:middle line:90%
or tapping on a point.

00:21:08.380 --> 00:21:10.740 align:middle line:84%
With energy medicine, energy
psychology techniques.

00:21:10.740 --> 00:21:13.840 align:middle line:84%
And these work below
the level of thought.

00:21:13.840 --> 00:21:16.610 align:middle line:84%
They work at the level of
the body's energy system.

00:21:16.610 --> 00:21:19.010 align:middle line:84%
What we see, for
example, on MRI or EEG

00:21:19.010 --> 00:21:24.430 align:middle line:84%
scans is massive shifts in
the body's usage of energy.

00:21:24.430 --> 00:21:28.270 align:middle line:84%
As you shift the energy of the
body, then the form of the body

00:21:28.270 --> 00:21:30.230 align:middle line:90%
shifts as well.

00:21:30.230 --> 00:21:32.930 align:middle line:84%
>> Profound because these are
