00:21:44.900 --> 00:21:45.980 align:middle line:90%
What is it?

00:21:45.980 --> 00:21:48.980 align:middle line:84%
And in your opinion, is this
one of the most effective

00:21:48.980 --> 00:21:52.940 align:middle line:84%
techniques people can learn to
use in order to, not only just

00:21:52.940 --> 00:21:56.540 align:middle line:84%
calm the body and the mind, but
get through things like trauma

00:21:56.540 --> 00:22:02.440 align:middle line:84%
or phobia or complex
trauma, like you said?

00:22:02.440 --> 00:22:04.430 align:middle line:84%
>> EFT is a very
simple technique.

00:22:04.430 --> 00:22:07.400 align:middle line:84%
It has you think about
something that bothers you.

00:22:07.400 --> 00:22:09.710 align:middle line:84%
Now when you think about
a thing that bothers you,

00:22:09.710 --> 00:22:11.810 align:middle line:84%
you're activating all the
circuits in your brain

00:22:11.810 --> 00:22:13.790 align:middle line:90%
that carry that information.

00:22:13.790 --> 00:22:18.320 align:middle line:84%
So you then have your brain
working in a certain way.

00:22:18.320 --> 00:22:20.480 align:middle line:84%
You have certain
circuits lit up.

00:22:20.480 --> 00:22:22.370 align:middle line:84%
If you think about
things that bother you

00:22:22.370 --> 00:22:24.770 align:middle line:84%
over and over and
over again, you

00:22:24.770 --> 00:22:27.170 align:middle line:84%
make those circuits bigger
and bigger and bigger.

00:22:27.170 --> 00:22:30.170 align:middle line:84%
But if you interrupt that
pattern with something else,

00:22:30.170 --> 00:22:33.230 align:middle line:84%
then you are able to
break that signaling.

00:22:33.230 --> 00:22:35.630 align:middle line:84%
And then your brain no
longer uses that circuit.

00:22:35.630 --> 00:22:38.900 align:middle line:84%
And the something else, in the
case of EFT, is acupressure.

00:22:38.900 --> 00:22:41.830 align:middle line:84%
There are over 300 meridian
points of the body.

00:22:41.830 --> 00:22:44.830 align:middle line:84%
They're organized into
14 meridian lines.

00:22:44.830 --> 00:22:48.230 align:middle line:84%
And EFT has you apply
acupressure in the form

00:22:48.230 --> 00:22:52.760 align:middle line:84%
of fingertip tapping like this
to about 13 of those points.

00:22:52.760 --> 00:22:55.370 align:middle line:84%
There are seven in the
brief form of EFT and 13

00:22:55.370 --> 00:22:58.610 align:middle line:84%
in the long form of EFT, as
well as using eye movements.

00:22:58.610 --> 00:23:02.270 align:middle line:84%
And what you see in
people's EEGs and MRIs when

00:23:02.270 --> 00:23:04.365 align:middle line:84%
they do this is
that, your first have

00:23:04.365 --> 00:23:05.743 align:middle line:90%
them think about the problem.

00:23:05.743 --> 00:23:07.160 align:middle line:84%
When they think
about the problem,

00:23:07.160 --> 00:23:09.620 align:middle line:84%
about the event in their
life, about the bomb blast,

00:23:09.620 --> 00:23:12.140 align:middle line:84%
about the car crash, about
the terrible divorce,

00:23:12.140 --> 00:23:16.040 align:middle line:84%
whatever it might be, you find
the emotional brain is all

00:23:16.040 --> 00:23:18.750 align:middle line:90%
lit up in an MRI or in an EEG.

00:23:18.750 --> 00:23:21.890 align:middle line:84%
You see all this activity
in the emotional midbrain.

00:23:21.890 --> 00:23:24.800 align:middle line:84%
When people start tapping,
it sends a second signal

00:23:24.800 --> 00:23:26.600 align:middle line:90%
