00:38:15.630 --> 00:38:19.420 align:middle line:90%
And the client said, six months.

00:38:19.420 --> 00:38:22.420 align:middle line:84%
And the therapist
thought to herself,

00:38:22.420 --> 00:38:26.590 align:middle line:84%
Mr. Right has been
working two cubicles away

00:38:26.590 --> 00:38:29.440 align:middle line:90%
from her for six months.

00:38:29.440 --> 00:38:32.800 align:middle line:84%
And she couldn't see him
because of her belief

00:38:32.800 --> 00:38:34.385 align:middle line:90%
that all the good men are taken.

00:38:34.385 --> 00:38:36.010 align:middle line:84%
And they actually
got married later on.

00:38:36.010 --> 00:38:38.427 align:middle line:84%
The therapist stayed in touch
with them for several years.

00:38:38.427 --> 00:38:40.090 align:middle line:84%
And they were a
perfectly happy couple.

00:38:40.090 --> 00:38:44.980 align:middle line:84%
So that belief was stopping her
from seeing her future husband

00:38:44.980 --> 00:38:47.450 align:middle line:84%
two cubicles away from
her for six months.

00:38:47.450 --> 00:38:49.180 align:middle line:84%
That's how powerful
beliefs can be.

00:38:49.180 --> 00:38:51.070 align:middle line:84%
Now when you're trapped
in negative belief

00:38:51.070 --> 00:38:54.250 align:middle line:84%
and you're trying to build
positive neural capacity

00:38:54.250 --> 00:38:56.530 align:middle line:90%
and new beliefs, it's hard.

00:38:56.530 --> 00:38:59.890 align:middle line:84%
Because your brain is used
to functioning in those ways.

00:38:59.890 --> 00:39:02.560 align:middle line:84%
We know from the work of Nobel
Prize winning professor, Eric

00:39:02.560 --> 00:39:06.970 align:middle line:84%
Kandel, that if you pass a
signal through a neural bundle

00:39:06.970 --> 00:39:09.985 align:middle line:84%
repeatedly for an hour, the
number of synapses can double,

00:39:09.985 --> 00:39:11.730 align:middle line:84%
or the number of
signaling hardware

00:39:11.730 --> 00:39:13.413 align:middle line:90%
can double in one hour.

00:39:13.413 --> 00:39:14.830 align:middle line:84%
And so what if
you've been passing

00:39:14.830 --> 00:39:16.390 align:middle line:84%
angry thoughts or
resentful thoughts

00:39:16.390 --> 00:39:18.490 align:middle line:84%
or guilty thoughts
or shameful thoughts

00:39:18.490 --> 00:39:21.530 align:middle line:84%
through those circuits for
years and years and years?

00:39:21.530 --> 00:39:24.130 align:middle line:84%
You now have massive
neural bundles dedicated

00:39:24.130 --> 00:39:25.690 align:middle line:90%
to sending those signals.

00:39:25.690 --> 00:39:29.440 align:middle line:84%
And now you think, gee,
I'm a miserable person.

00:39:29.440 --> 00:39:31.210 align:middle line:90%
I'm horrible to my kids.

00:39:31.210 --> 00:39:33.250 align:middle line:90%
I abuse my wife.

00:39:33.250 --> 00:39:34.720 align:middle line:90%
I miserable on my job.

00:39:34.720 --> 00:39:37.750 align:middle line:84%
I keep on having
financial disasters.

00:39:37.750 --> 00:39:40.880 align:middle line:84%
I'll go take a weekend
workshop at the Dawson Church,

00:39:40.880 --> 00:39:43.865 align:middle line:84%
or Bruce Lipton or Deepak
Chopra or someone like that.

00:39:43.865 --> 00:39:46.240 align:middle line:84%
And so they go to a Tony
Robbins workshop or Jody Spencer

00:39:46.240 --> 00:39:48.900 align:middle line:84%
workshop or a Marianne
Williamson workshop.

00:39:48.900 --> 00:39:51.880 align:middle line:84%
And now you feel great
after the workshop.

00:39:51.880 --> 00:39:54.460 align:middle line:84%
You're in this temporary
state of euphoria.

00:39:54.460 --> 00:39:56.250 align:middle line:90%
You feel so good.

00:39:56.250 --> 00:40:00.820 align:middle line:84%
But then Monday morning, you're
back in your regular life

00:40:00.820 --> 00:40:03.250 align:middle line:84%
with all the
stimuli that trigger

00:40:03.250 --> 00:40:05.680 align:middle line:84%
the firing of those neural
bundles which you've been

00:40:05.680 --> 00:40:08.120 align:middle line:90%
building for the last 30 years.

00:40:08.120 --> 00:40:10.368 align:middle line:84%
And you revert right
back to the way you are.

00:40:10.368 --> 00:40:12.160 align:middle line:84%
So that's the challenge
of personal growth.

00:40:12.160 --> 00:40:14.680 align:middle line:84%
We have to build that
signaling capacity.

00:40:14.680 --> 00:40:16.810 align:middle line:90%
We have to build that belief.

00:40:16.810 --> 00:40:19.750 align:middle line:84%
We have to build those
positive circuits,

00:40:19.750 --> 00:40:22.990 align:middle line:84%
even before we have
the experience of them.

00:40:22.990 --> 00:40:24.220 align:middle line:90%
And that requires discipline.

00:40:24.220 --> 00:40:26.620 align:middle line:84%
That's why we need meditation,
why we need tapping,

00:40:26.620 --> 00:40:28.670 align:middle line:84%
why we need to stick
with it over time.

00:40:28.670 --> 00:40:31.240 align:middle line:84%
But if you stick with it over
time, good things happen.

00:40:31.240 --> 00:40:33.460 align:middle line:84%
You build that
positive neural bundle

00:40:33.460 --> 00:40:36.370 align:middle line:84%
that was so tiny at first, gets
bigger and bigger and bigger.

00:40:36.370 --> 00:40:39.670 align:middle line:84%
And the cool thing about it
is, even if you've been angry

00:40:39.670 --> 00:40:44.200 align:middle line:84%
for 50 years and you have a
gigantic neural bundle devoted

00:40:44.200 --> 00:40:48.820 align:middle line:84%
to that, the other
flip side of the coin

00:40:48.820 --> 00:40:51.910 align:middle line:84%
is that, if you don't use
the neural bundle for three

00:40:51.910 --> 00:40:54.110 align:middle line:90%
weeks, your body notices.

00:40:54.110 --> 00:40:57.902 align:middle line:84%
It's like it notices that
you're not using that wiring

00:40:57.902 --> 00:40:59.110 align:middle line:90%
and begins to disassemble it.

00:40:59.110 --> 00:41:01.840 align:middle line:84%
So within three
weeks, it says, gee.

00:41:01.840 --> 00:41:04.000 align:middle line:84%
He's not using the
anger circuit anymore.

00:41:04.000 --> 00:41:06.950 align:middle line:84%
We have better uses
for those molecules.

00:41:06.950 --> 00:41:10.060 align:middle line:84%
It then repurpose those
to build new circuits.

00:41:10.060 --> 00:41:13.630 align:middle line:84%
So our brains are
in this dynamic flow

00:41:13.630 --> 00:41:17.230 align:middle line:84%
of rewiring with every
thought and every moment.

00:41:17.230 --> 00:41:19.000 align:middle line:84%
And so if you have
negative beliefs,

00:41:19.000 --> 00:41:22.450 align:middle line:84%
if you quit thinking
those thoughts,

00:41:22.450 --> 00:41:24.220 align:middle line:84%
adding fuel to the
fire, emotional fuel

00:41:24.220 --> 00:41:27.070 align:middle line:84%
to the fire that is
signaling those circuits,

00:41:27.070 --> 00:41:28.480 align:middle line:90%
they start to change.

00:41:28.480 --> 00:41:32.320 align:middle line:84%
In studies of long term,
long term meditators,

00:41:32.320 --> 00:41:34.840 align:middle line:84%
research shows that
their brains start

00:41:34.840 --> 00:41:36.110 align:middle line:90%
to function very differently.

00:41:36.110 --> 00:41:38.500 align:middle line:84%
The amygdala, which is
the brain's fire alarms,

00:41:38.500 --> 00:41:40.810 align:middle line:84%
the main organ which
sends that stress

00:41:40.810 --> 00:41:43.130 align:middle line:84%
signal throughout
your whole body,

00:41:43.130 --> 00:41:48.070 align:middle line:84%
it literally atrophies
in long term meditators.

00:41:48.070 --> 00:41:50.230 align:middle line:84%
Because they're not
using those signals.

00:41:50.230 --> 00:41:55.510 align:middle line:84%
And the circuits of joy,
of happiness, of peace,

00:41:55.510 --> 00:41:57.580 align:middle line:84%
of emotion regulation,
begin to grow.

00:41:57.580 --> 00:42:02.410 align:middle line:84%
In one of the case histories
in my book "Mind to Matter,"

00:42:02.410 --> 00:42:06.430 align:middle line:84%
the man in this case
history was a TV host

00:42:06.430 --> 00:42:08.010 align:middle line:90%
and an astrophysicist.

00:42:08.010 --> 00:42:10.150 align:middle line:84%
And he'd heard that
meditation produced benefits.

00:42:10.150 --> 00:42:12.170 align:middle line:84%
So he thought,
I'll give it a try.

00:42:12.170 --> 00:42:14.560 align:middle line:84%
But he had a TV crew with
him, went into a university

00:42:14.560 --> 00:42:17.170 align:middle line:84%
laboratory, and had a
comprehensive workup

00:42:17.170 --> 00:42:20.770 align:middle line:84%
of his reaction times, his
stress levels, his hormones,

00:42:20.770 --> 00:42:21.920 align:middle line:90%
his brain function.

00:42:21.920 --> 00:42:24.070 align:middle line:84%
And in a high
resolution MRI, they

00:42:24.070 --> 00:42:26.590 align:middle line:84%
measured the volume of
every part of his brain.

00:42:26.590 --> 00:42:28.990 align:middle line:84%
He then began to
meditate, be mindful.

00:42:28.990 --> 00:42:31.630 align:middle line:84%
So week after week
after week, he

00:42:31.630 --> 00:42:33.640 align:middle line:84%
began to feel more
and more peaceful.

00:42:33.640 --> 00:42:36.760 align:middle line:84%
He went back into the
lab after eight weeks

00:42:36.760 --> 00:42:38.860 align:middle line:90%
of mindfulness practice.

00:42:38.860 --> 00:42:42.280 align:middle line:84%
And they measured the volume of
each part of his brain again.

00:42:42.280 --> 00:42:48.580 align:middle line:84%
And some parts had grown by
2%, 3%, 4% in just eight weeks.

00:42:48.580 --> 00:42:51.940 align:middle line:84%
But the part that grew the most
was a part of the hippocampus,

00:42:51.940 --> 00:42:54.920 align:middle line:84%
that emotional midbrain
called the dentate gyrus.

00:42:54.920 --> 00:42:57.310 align:middle line:84%
And the dentate gyrus's
job is to coordinate

00:42:57.310 --> 00:43:00.970 align:middle line:84%
emotional regulation among
multiple brain regions.

00:43:00.970 --> 00:43:08.400 align:middle line:84%
His dentate gyrus, in
eight weeks, grew by 22.8.

00:43:08.400 --> 00:43:09.960 align:middle line:90%
Now think about that.

00:43:09.960 --> 00:43:13.500 align:middle line:84%
In just eight weeks of
changing consciousness,

00:43:13.500 --> 00:43:16.650 align:middle line:84%
of changing mind, the
matter of his brain,

00:43:16.650 --> 00:43:19.080 align:middle line:84%
and in particular,
the part of the brain

00:43:19.080 --> 00:43:22.680 align:middle line:84%
responsible for regulating
emotion, reducing stress,

00:43:22.680 --> 00:43:25.900 align:middle line:90%
that grew by 22.8%.

00:43:25.900 --> 00:43:27.450 align:middle line:90%
It did not take 10,000 hours.

00:43:27.450 --> 00:43:29.120 align:middle line:84%
Did not take 10
years of practice.

00:43:29.120 --> 00:43:32.610 align:middle line:84%
In just eight weeks, we
can trigger remodeling

00:43:32.610 --> 00:43:33.868 align:middle line:90%
of our neural tissue.

00:43:33.868 --> 00:43:35.410 align:middle line:84%
And then we have a
much happier life.

00:43:35.410 --> 00:43:39.180 align:middle line:84%
Increased emotion regulation
means, I don't yell at my kids.

00:43:39.180 --> 00:43:42.030 align:middle line:84%
I don't give people the finger
and have road rage when I'm

00:43:42.030 --> 00:43:44.172 align:middle line:90%
driving to work in the morning.

00:43:44.172 --> 00:43:45.630 align:middle line:84%
I'm not screaming
at my colleagues.

00:43:45.630 --> 00:43:50.220 align:middle line:84%
I'm not causing my heart to
race and raising my cortisol

00:43:50.220 --> 00:43:51.220 align:middle line:90%
with stress.

00:43:51.220 --> 00:43:53.280 align:middle line:90%
Emotion regulation is key.

00:43:53.280 --> 00:43:56.098 align:middle line:84%
And you do it much better
when you build those circuits.

00:43:56.098 --> 00:43:57.390 align:middle line:90%
So we can build those circuits.

00:43:57.390 --> 00:44:00.100 align:middle line:84%
They then change the whole
experience we have of life.

00:44:00.100 --> 00:44:03.770 align:middle line:84%
But you have to start building
them in the absence of them.

00:44:03.770 --> 00:44:05.670 align:middle line:84%
So you aren't a peaceful
person at first.

00:44:05.670 --> 00:44:08.520 align:middle line:84%
And you have to practice
over and over and over again

00:44:08.520 --> 00:44:11.700 align:middle line:84%
and prioritize being peaceful,
being happy, being optimistic

00:44:11.700 --> 00:44:13.120 align:middle line:90%
over those old habits.

00:44:13.120 --> 00:44:14.440 align:middle line:90%
It takes a while to do that.

00:44:14.440 --> 00:44:16.170 align:middle line:90%
That's why it's called practice.

00:44:16.170 --> 00:44:18.467 align:middle line:84%
But build those
circuits long enough,

00:44:18.467 --> 00:44:20.050 align:middle line:84%
they get bigger and
bigger and bigger.

00:44:20.050 --> 00:44:22.390 align:middle line:84%
And then all those circuits
of stress and anger

00:44:22.390 --> 00:44:24.100 align:middle line:90%
just start to go away.

00:44:24.100 --> 00:44:25.590 align:middle line:90%
You might look the same.

00:44:25.590 --> 00:44:27.580 align:middle line:84%
Your face might look the
same after a few weeks

00:44:27.580 --> 00:44:28.380 align:middle line:90%
of doing this.

00:44:28.380 --> 00:44:32.250 align:middle line:84%
Inside your brain, you
have a whole new brain.

00:44:32.250 --> 00:44:36.660 align:middle line:84%
A friend of mine named Beth was
diagnosed with breast cancer.

00:44:36.660 --> 00:44:40.970 align:middle line:84%
And they found a lump on
the top of her right breast.

00:44:40.970 --> 00:44:43.440 align:middle line:84%
Eventually, it was measured
at five centimeters

00:44:43.440 --> 00:44:45.750 align:middle line:90%
across, big, solid tumor.

00:44:45.750 --> 00:44:48.360 align:middle line:84%
She was being treated by a
famous cancer clinic called

00:44:48.360 --> 00:44:51.360 align:middle line:84%
MD Anderson in Houston,
Texas and having

00:44:51.360 --> 00:44:54.738 align:middle line:84%
great oncologists, great
surgeons, great staff there.

00:44:54.738 --> 00:44:56.280 align:middle line:84%
Once they found the
tumor, they began

00:44:56.280 --> 00:44:58.800 align:middle line:84%
to look for signs
of the cancer having

00:44:58.800 --> 00:45:01.055 align:middle line:90%
spread beyond the primary site.

00:45:01.055 --> 00:45:02.430 align:middle line:84%
And they found
that all the lymph

00:45:02.430 --> 00:45:05.160 align:middle line:84%
nodes under her right
armpit near the tumor

00:45:05.160 --> 00:45:06.060 align:middle line:90%
were all in flame.

00:45:06.060 --> 00:45:09.690 align:middle line:84%
It looked as though cancer cells
were filling those lymph nodes.

00:45:09.690 --> 00:45:12.795 align:middle line:84%
Now when cancer gets into your
lymph system, it's bad news.

00:45:12.795 --> 00:45:13.920 align:middle line:90%
It's like your bloodstream.

00:45:13.920 --> 00:45:15.640 align:middle line:84%
It goes all
throughout your body.

00:45:15.640 --> 00:45:19.020 align:middle line:84%
And once the cells, cancer
cells get into the lymph system,

00:45:19.020 --> 00:45:20.520 align:middle line:84%
they can travel
throughout the body

00:45:20.520 --> 00:45:24.030 align:middle line:84%
and produce secondary tumors
in other parts of your system.

00:45:24.030 --> 00:45:26.730 align:middle line:84%
And they then also found
three spots of inflammation

00:45:26.730 --> 00:45:27.900 align:middle line:90%
on her right lung.

00:45:27.900 --> 00:45:30.180 align:middle line:84%
So it looked as though the
process had already begun.

00:45:30.180 --> 00:45:32.220 align:middle line:84%
In fact, the diagnosis
was so serious

00:45:32.220 --> 00:45:34.890 align:middle line:84%
that the day she got
it, the oncologist,

00:45:34.890 --> 00:45:37.830 align:middle line:84%
the cancer surgeon said
to Beth, in her office,

00:45:37.830 --> 00:45:40.320 align:middle line:84%
she said, Beth,
normally we'd want you

00:45:40.320 --> 00:45:41.770 align:middle line:90%
on chemotherapy and radiation.

00:45:41.770 --> 00:45:44.100 align:middle line:90%
We'd schedule you for that soon.

00:45:44.100 --> 00:45:46.950 align:middle line:84%
This is so serious, I wanted
to go straight from my office

00:45:46.950 --> 00:45:51.330 align:middle line:84%
right now to radiology
for your first treatment.

00:45:51.330 --> 00:45:57.000 align:middle line:84%
Now Beth said-- to her credit,
said, I need time to think.

00:45:57.000 --> 00:45:57.840 align:middle line:90%
This is my body.

00:45:57.840 --> 00:45:59.000 align:middle line:90%
These are my choices.

00:45:59.000 --> 00:46:01.000 align:middle line:84%
I need to just step back
from this for a moment.

00:46:01.000 --> 00:46:03.450 align:middle line:84%
So she did not go
straight to radiology.

00:46:03.450 --> 00:46:06.510 align:middle line:84%
And so she called friends
and e-mailed people like me

00:46:06.510 --> 00:46:08.610 align:middle line:84%
and said, I've had
this diagnosis.

00:46:08.610 --> 00:46:09.870 align:middle line:90%
What do I do?

00:46:09.870 --> 00:46:12.360 align:middle line:84%
She got a lot of help, a
lot of recommendations.

00:46:12.360 --> 00:46:16.020 align:middle line:84%
And she decided to use
energy on her issue

00:46:16.020 --> 00:46:18.180 align:middle line:90%
before conventional treatment.

00:46:18.180 --> 00:46:20.910 align:middle line:84%
And she cleaned up all of
the stress in her life.

00:46:20.910 --> 00:46:23.460 align:middle line:84%
She turned off the
alerts on her cell phone.

00:46:23.460 --> 00:46:24.900 align:middle line:90%
She quit watching the news.

00:46:24.900 --> 00:46:29.760 align:middle line:84%
She quit any kind of input
that could upset her or produce

00:46:29.760 --> 00:46:31.080 align:middle line:90%
stress in her body.

00:46:31.080 --> 00:46:32.340 align:middle line:90%
She began to do Qigong.

00:46:32.340 --> 00:46:33.990 align:middle line:90%
She did EFT tapping.

00:46:33.990 --> 00:46:36.090 align:middle line:84%
She really amped up her
meditation practice.

00:46:36.090 --> 00:46:37.250 align:middle line:90%
She cleaned up her diet.

00:46:37.250 --> 00:46:40.320 align:middle line:84%
Her diet was pretty good, but
she made her diet impeccable.

00:46:40.320 --> 00:46:42.990 align:middle line:84%
She did everything
possible to help herself.

00:46:42.990 --> 00:46:47.040 align:middle line:84%
So she got this
diagnosis in March.

00:46:47.040 --> 00:46:51.840 align:middle line:84%
She went back into the
hospital in May for a follow up

00:46:51.840 --> 00:46:53.790 align:middle line:90%
eight weeks later.

00:46:53.790 --> 00:46:59.260 align:middle line:84%
And all the lymph nodes on
her right armpit were clear.

00:46:59.260 --> 00:47:03.660 align:middle line:84%
The tumor had shrunk from 5
centimeters to 1.4 centimeters.

00:47:03.660 --> 00:47:05.660 align:middle line:84%
Now of course, the doctor
said, well, let's just

00:47:05.660 --> 00:47:08.100 align:middle line:84%
stay with the surgery right
now and we'll cut that out.

00:47:08.100 --> 00:47:10.823 align:middle line:90%
And Beth said, I don't think so.

00:47:10.823 --> 00:47:12.990 align:middle line:84%
She also called me right
after she got the diagnosis

00:47:12.990 --> 00:47:16.080 align:middle line:84%
and said, Dawson,
I've had a gene test.

00:47:16.080 --> 00:47:19.020 align:middle line:84%
And I have eight defective
genes, some of which

00:47:19.020 --> 00:47:21.070 align:middle line:90%
predispose me to breast cancer.

00:47:21.070 --> 00:47:23.050 align:middle line:84%
And I said her,
well, Beth, you have

00:47:23.050 --> 00:47:25.410 align:middle line:90%
24,000 genes in your cells.

00:47:25.410 --> 00:47:30.900 align:middle line:84%
That means you have
23,992 that are just fine.

00:47:30.900 --> 00:47:32.226 align:middle line:90%
Let's work with those.

00:47:32.226 --> 00:47:36.810 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHING]

00:47:36.810 --> 00:47:39.090 align:middle line:84%
So again, she did
all these things

00:47:39.090 --> 00:47:42.270 align:middle line:84%
to raise, elevate her mood,
to make herself happier,

00:47:42.270 --> 00:47:43.440 align:middle line:90%
to shift her energy.

00:47:43.440 --> 00:47:46.680 align:middle line:84%
And within just eight
weeks, that big change

00:47:46.680 --> 00:47:49.320 align:middle line:84%
had happened with the tumor
shrinking and her lymph nodes

00:47:49.320 --> 00:47:50.270 align:middle line:90%
being clear.

00:47:50.270 --> 00:47:52.050 align:middle line:84%
Later on blood tests
showed there was not

00:47:52.050 --> 00:47:53.548 align:middle line:90%
a trace of cancer in her body.

00:47:53.548 --> 00:47:55.590 align:middle line:84%
And it's been several
years now and there's still

00:47:55.590 --> 00:47:56.880 align:middle line:90%
